data.title: Rafael Osuna
data.meta_description:
Arranger, Composer, Singer, Saxophonist, Flutist, Clarinetist, music producer and conductor, he was born in Caracas on October 22, 1959. He has studied harmony and composition with maestro JUAN DOMENE, saxophone and clarinet with teachers BENJAMÌN BREA and HAROLD GALLARDO, trumpet with maestro RAUL AG
RAZ and trombone with maestro ALBANYS CASTRO.
 He is or has been a member of: BANDA DEL MINISTERIO DE LA DEFENSA (clarinetist), BANDA MARCIAL CARACAS (saxophonist), ORQUESTA DE PORFI JIMÈNEZ (singer), ORQUESTA CARONI DE LA GUARDIA NACIONAL (arranger), record label VELVET DE VENEZUELA (music producer ), ORQUESTA SINFÒNICA VENEZUELA (arranger and music producer), ORQUESTA TIPICA DEL TECNOLÒGICO DE ACARIGUA EDO PORTUGUESA (arranger), PLANET RECORDS record label (music producer), RECORDLAND record label (music producer), V&L PRODUCCIONES record label (music producer), VEDISCO USA record label (music producer), “CARLOS MOLL” SYMPHONY ORCHESTRA MATURIN EDO MONAGAS (arranger), among others; In addition, as a musical producer, he has to his credit more than 90 albums, among which are: 8 albums for the ORQUESTA SINFÒNICA VENEZUELA and 2 for the BILLOS CARACAS BOYS, he is currently the lead singer of his own orchestra OSUNA BANDA SHOW and eventually is director guest of CONCERT BANDS and SYMPHONIC ORCHESTAS such as: ARAGUA SYMPHONIC ORCHESTRA, EDO MERIDA CONCERT BAND, LA GRITA CONCERT BAND EDO TACHIRA, BIELORUSIA PRESIDENCY SYMPHONIC ORCHESTRA, and EDO DE CONCERT BAND, among others. .
